        <section id="accordionsMarkup">
            <header class="content-block bg-light-grey">
                <div class="container">
                    <h3>Choices Select structure</h3>
                    <p>The Choices Select element uses the feature rich <a href="https://github.com/jshjohnson/Choices" target="_blank"><code>choices.js</code></a> library to wrap an ordinary select dropdown.</p>
                    <p>A Choices Select element is created using an existing select and the Choices Select js module <code>data-js-module="choicesSelect"</code>.</p>
                    <p>A Choices Select element options are defined by the <code>data-options</code> attribute, which accepts a JSON string in the following format:</p>
                    <pre>
                        [
                          {
                            "value": "1",
                            "label": "One",
                            "customProperties": {
                              "description": "One"
                            }
                          },
                          {
                            "value": "2",
                            "label": "Two",
                            "customProperties": {
                              "description": "Two"
                            }
                          }
                        ]
                    </pre>
                    <p>Where <code>value</code> is the value of the option, <code>label</code> is what is displayed and <code>customProperties.description</code> is what is searchable.</p>
                    <p>A Choices Select element default option is defined by the <code>data-default</code> attribute, which accepts the value of one of your JSON options.</p>
                    <p>You can also specify the css classes to style the outer and inner containers via the <code>data-container-outer-class</code> and <code>data-container-inner-class</code> attributes; applying the <code>.choices-select .form__field</code> and <code>.form__control</code> classes, respectively, will give the Choices Select element the same styling as other form elements.</p>

{{> snippet-choices-select }}

